    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS FULLER RT-610 SERIES - REASSEMBLE</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcsubsec>
        <title>REASSEMBLE</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="6">
            <title>LOW SPEED GEAR AND OUTPUT SHAFT ASSEMBLY</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Make sure the magnet is installed in the recess in the auxiliary case.</para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Mark the timing teeth on the low speed gear. Mark any two adjacent gear teeth on the low
                    speed gear. Then mark the two adjacent teeth which are directly opposite the first set marked. There
                    should be the same number of teeth between the markings on each side of the gear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302476">Figure 76</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302476" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302476" filename="../figg13/G1302476.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 76. Mark Teeth on Gear</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Place the splined spacer in the hub of the low speed gear, shoulder toward the rear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302477">Figure 77</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302477" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302477" filename="../figg13/G1302477.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 77. Place Splined Spacer in Hub of Low Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the low speed gear and spacer over the rear of the shaft and against the
                    shoulder, clutching teeth to the front (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302478">Figure 78</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302478" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302478" filename="../figg13/G1302478.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 78. Install Low Speed Gear and Spacer Over Rear of Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install the low speed gear rear washer on the shaft and against the gear, chamfer to the
                    rear (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302479">Figure 79</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302479" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302479" filename="../figg13/G1302479.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 79. Install Low Speed Gear Rear Washer</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Set the output shaft with the forward end down and place the auxiliary housing over the
                    rear of the shaft so that the shaft extends through the rear bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302480">Figure 80</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302480" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302480" filename="../figg13/G1302480.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 80. Place Auxiliary Housing Over Rear of Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Seat the mainshaft rear bearing securely on the shaft and in the bore (
                    <hotlnk xrefid="f1302481">Figure 81</hotlnk>).
                </para>
            </step1>
            <figure id="f1302481" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1302481" filename="../figg13/G1302481.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 81. Seat Mainshaft Rear Bearing on Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
